<paragraph blockId="16.[227,345,1034,1056]" box="[227,345,1034,1060]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,345,1034,1060]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[227,1437,1081,1213]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
The male of 
<emphasis box="[386,542,1081,1107]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
D. 
<taxonomicName box="[425,542,1081,1107]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Ballomma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neethlingi">neethlingi</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
gen. et sp. nov. is easily recognized by the field of spines in front of the epigastric fold and the palp with a retrolateral patellar swelling and a broad triangular transparent RTA. The female has a characteristic epigyne in which the ducts in transparency are in the shape of an X with a slight extension where upper and lower parts of X meet.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
