<paragraph blockId="16.[227,1436,2000,2062]" lastBlockId="17.[227,1436,305,401]" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="18" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
COLOUR. Carapace, sternum and chelicerae medium brown without silvery setae (
<figureCitation box="[1158,1237,2000,2026]" captionStart="Fig. 11" captionStartId="17.[227,270,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[227,1436,587,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[227,1436,587,1904]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 11. Ballomma neethlingi gen. et sp. nov. A – C. Paratype, ♂ (NCA 76 / 1048) D – E. Holotype, ♀. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. As preceding, ventral view. C. As preceding, detail. D. Habitus, dorsal view. E. As preceding, ventral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1406694/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
<collectionCode box="[1237,1261,2000,2026]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">A</collectionCode>
– 
<collectionCode box="[1278,1299,2000,2026]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">C</collectionCode>
); chelicerae slightly darker at base than in distal half; legs pale yellowish brown; abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[1181,1265,2035,2062]" captionStart="Fig. 11" captionStartId="17.[227,270,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[227,1436,587,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[227,1436,587,1904]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 11. Ballomma neethlingi gen. et sp. nov. A – C. Paratype, ♂ (NCA 76 / 1048) D – E. Holotype, ♀. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. As preceding, ventral view. C. As preceding, detail. D. Habitus, dorsal view. E. As preceding, ventral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1406694/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
<collectionCode box="[1265,1289,2036,2062]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">A</collectionCode>
– 
<collectionCode box="[1306,1326,2036,2062]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">B</collectionCode>
): dorsum and sides pale with complex dark pattern on dorsum hidden by paler suffusion, provided with four dark apodemes; venter pale with complex dark pattern, yellow sclerotized area in front of epigastric fold; spinnerets pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[227,1436,441,503]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
CARAPACE. Smooth (
<figureCitation box="[458,539,441,467]" captionStart="Fig. 11" captionStartId="17.[227,270,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[227,1436,587,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[227,1436,587,1904]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 11. Ballomma neethlingi gen. et sp. nov. A – C. Paratype, ♂ (NCA 76 / 1048) D – E. Holotype, ♀. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. As preceding, ventral view. C. As preceding, detail. D. Habitus, dorsal view. E. As preceding, ventral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1406694/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
