– 
<collectionCode box="[477,497,718,744]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">E</collectionCode>
): dorsum and sides pale with complex dark pattern; venter pale with few dark spots; spinnerets pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[227,1437,818,915]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
CARAPACE (
<figureCitation box="[357,439,818,845]" captionStart="Fig. 11" captionStartId="17.[227,270,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[227,1436,587,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[227,1436,587,1904]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 11. Ballomma neethlingi gen. et sp. nov. A – C. Paratype, ♂ (NCA 76 / 1048) D – E. Holotype, ♀. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. As preceding, ventral view. C. As preceding, detail. D. Habitus, dorsal view. E. As preceding, ventral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1406694/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
<collectionCode box="[439,463,818,844]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D</collectionCode>
